sql:
SELECT DISTINCT p.provider_name, s.service_name
FROM providers p
INNER JOIN analytics_services s ON p.provider_id = s.provider_id;

SELECT cookies.*, providers.*
FROM cookies
JOIN providers ON cookies.provider_id = providers.provider_id;

external_knowledge:
- Secure and HttpOnly are attributes of cookies that enhance their security;
- In the metaphor, "locked" refers to secure cookies, while "hidden under the ground" refers to HttpOnly cookies;
- The sparkle's duration represents the cookie's storage duration.

; "cookie purpose" refers to the reason for which the cookie is used;
; "type" indicates the category or class of the cookie;
; "domain" is the website or service for which the cookie is intended;

- 'Analytics cookies' are used to track website usage and provide insights into user behavior;
- 'Google Ireland Limited' is a key part of the Google corporation responsible for European operations;
- 'Agreed to allow' here means consent status is 'granted'.

sql:
SELECT a.service_name, p.provider_name
FROM analytics_services a
INNER JOIN providers p ON a.provider_id = p.provider_id;

